\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces The escalation decision. A human delegates a task to an LLM agent, which produces a prediction and then decides whether to implement (incurring error cost $c_w$ if wrong) or escalate (incurring labor cost $c_\ell $). The agent escalates when its estimated probability of being correct $\hat  {p}$ falls below a threshold $\tau $.}}{2}{figure.caption.1}\protected@file@percent }
\providecommand*\caption@xref[2]{\@setref\relax\@undefined{#1}}
\newlabel{fig:workflow}{{1}{2}{The escalation decision. A human delegates a task to an LLM agent, which produces a prediction and then decides whether to implement (incurring error cost $c_w$ if wrong) or escalate (incurring labor cost $c_\ell $). The agent escalates when its estimated probability of being correct $\hat {p}$ falls below a threshold $\tau $}{figure.caption.1}{}}
